            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-17T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-17T17:00:00-05:00" n="156" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/2–1548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Cuba</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-17T17:00:00-05:00">February 17, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>226. For Clayton from Lovett. Senate Foreign Relations Committee has approved
                    provision in <gloss target="#t_ERP1">ERP</gloss> legislation requiring inclusion
                    in bilateral agreements of a commitment that participating countries (which
                    include western Germany) must cooperate with each other in stimulating
                    interchange of goods and reducing trade barriers among themselves. You may
                    advise <gloss target="#t_ERP1">ERP</gloss> countries that we would expect clause
                    such as you suggest ur 196 Feb 15 in bilatetal <gloss target="#t_ERP1">ERP</gloss> agreements, as part of implementation this policy. You may also
                    advise Chinese Del that we would expect similar provision in China aid bilateral
                    agreement. [Lovett.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
